description: As Gotham continues to fall apart with the Joker King's plan in full effect, Batman and his allies attempt to put a stop to the madness!
name: 10,000 Clowns: Lights of Gotham

description: A collection of issues 1-6 of the Nodwick comic book. Join Nodwick the henchman and his employers Yeagar the inebriated warrior, Artax the absent-minded wizard, and Piffany the innocent cleric as they confront dragons, gods, and the occasional war.

DC NATION is back with an all-new, Bat-tacular issue!

Enjoy exciting holiday adventures with your favorite DC heroes (and villains)!

Featuring an exclusive sneak peek at the much-anticipated new series Beware The Batman!
Collects Invincible Iron Man #2-3, Avengers: The Initiative #16 & Mighty Avengers #16.
Collects Avengers: The Initiative #17, Mighty Avengers #17, Invincible Iron Man #4 & Iron Man #33.
Collects Mighty Avengers #18, Avengers: The Initiative #18, Iron Man #34 & Invincible Iron Man #5.

A single dollar will get you the original tale of vampiric terror that started it all off! 30 Days of Night put IDW on the comics-publishing map and established Steve Niles and Ben Templesmith as creative forces to be reckoned with. Now, you can return to Barrow, or visit it for the first time, as the sun goes down on the remote Alaskan town... and then check out the next page for the latest bloody happenings in the 30 Days world!

volume.name: Hundred Penny Press: 30 Days of Night

description: Can you make an exciting comic out of insomnia? Kevin Huizenga rises to the challenge as he depicts his alter ego Glenn Ganges wrestling with sleeplessness, trying to trick it by reading a particularly abstruse book, obsessively breaking his past, present and future life into ever more hallucinatory, complex grids, and wandering around his darkened house trying not to wake up his wife. Also: Loose cat action!

1. Let the Dreamer Beware (written by Jerry Siegel)

2. Barf the Insurance Salesman (written by Bill Pearson)

3. Curse of the Yeti! (written by Otto Binder)

4. The Skin Eaters (written by Terry Bisson)
name: Let the Dreamer Beware
